  "text": "The ext_authz filter in Envoy v1.31.2 implements bypass and passthrough logic through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. PER-ROUTE BYPASS CONFIGURATION:\nThe FilterConfigPerRoute class (ext_authz.h) stores per-route configuration with a disabled() method that controls whether authorization checks are bypassed for specific routes. The FilterConfig class also implements filterEnabled() method that checks global filter enable/disable status via metadata matchers and runtime flags.\n\n2. BYPASS LOGIC FLOW:\nIn Filter::decodeHeaders() (ext_authz.cc:226), the skip_check_ flag is set by calling getPerRouteFlags() (ext_authz.cc:810), which resolves the most specific per-route configuration. If skip_check_ is true (line 230-231), the filter immediately returns Continue, bypassing authorization checks without calling initiateCall().\n\n3. ROUTE CACHE CLEARING:\nThe clearRouteCache() configuration (ext_authz.h:73) and corresponding clear_route_cache_ field (ext_authz.h:180) control whether the route cache should be invalidated when authorization responses modify request headers. This is implemented in Filter::onComplete() (ext_authz.cc:434-442) where the cache is cleared if response headers modify the request.\n\n4. IMMEDIATE RESPONSE PATH:\nThe Filter::onComplete() method (ext_authz.cc:403) handles authorization responses immediately upon completion. The initiating_call_ flag (ext_authz.h:365) distinguishes between synchronous (stack-based) and asynchronous callbacks. The Response struct (common/ext_authz.h:86) contains all header mutations that can be applied immediately to both upstream and downstream responses.\n\n5. COMMON AUTHORIZATION HANDLING:\nThe common ext_authz implementation provides the Response struct with comprehensive header mutation support (headers_to_add, headers_to_set, headers_to_append, headers_to_remove) for both request upstream and response downstream paths. The CheckRequestUtils class creates authorization check requests that are sent via either HTTP (RawHttpClientImpl) or gRPC (GrpcClientImpl) clients.\n\n6. HTTP/GRPC CLIENT IMPLEMENTATIONS:\nRawHttpClientImpl (ext_authz_http_impl.h) and GrpcClientImpl (ext_authz_grpc_impl.h) both implement the Client interface and handle authorization responses. Their onSuccess() callbacks process the CheckResponse and trigger the immediate response path through RequestCallbacks::onComplete().\n\n7. NETWORK FILTER SUPPORT:\nThe network ext_authz filter (source/extensions/filters/network/ext_authz/) provides similar bypass and decision caching mechanisms at the TCP connection level through its Config class and Filter::onComplete() implementation.\n\nAll per-route configuration is created via ExtAuthzFilterConfig::createRouteSpecificFilterConfigTyped() (config.cc:72), which instantiates FilterConfigPerRoute objects that allow bypassing checks at the virtual host, route, or weighted cluster level."
}

